`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The key design insight here: `GridCellComponent` isn't being removed from the ECS - it's being *decoupled from world.ts*. We keep `gridCell` in the Entity interface (just without the LEGACY label), but move the query to each callsite with `world.with("gridCell", "position")`. Miniplex queries created at module-level work identically to those exported from world.ts - they register with the same world singleton.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
