`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The key pattern discovered: when a centralized Miniplex query is removed from `world.ts`, the `world.with()` call moves to each callsite at module level. This is transparent to Miniplex (same world singleton, same registration). The subtle trap is test mocks — any file that mocks `@/game/ecs/world` with a bare `world: { ... }` object must add `with: () => mockQuery` because module-level query creation runs at **import time**, before test setup.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

